<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-18T11:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-18T11:41:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 123G31/112</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-18T18:00:00+01:19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 19, 2.29
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2239. Your 1074, April 1, 1918. Spanish Embassy reports German
                            authorities state that threat to seize Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">Gerard</persName>’s property due to misunderstanding, and that
                            German Government is disposed to respect property of American diplomatic
                            and consular officers in Germany on basis of reciprocity.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>